==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Entremets
<hw>En`tre*mets"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. sing. & pl.</pos>
<ety>[F., fr. <ets>entre</ets> between + <ets>mets</ets> a dish,
mess.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Cookery)</fld> <def>A side dish; a dainty
or relishing dish usually eaten after the joints or principal dish;
also, a sweetmeat, served with a dinner.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Any small entertainment between two greater
ones.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>entrench</ent>⟦br⟧
